ing with Diversity:</strong> How to Live in a Complicated World: This talk is based on the upcoming book, Mind Over Manners: Etiquette for a Diverse Society. The focus is not so much on demographic diversity, but of diversity of values, priorities, and life experiences.  What courtesies do parents and the childless, pet owners and the dog-phobic, vegans and omnivores, the healthy and the sick, owe each other?";}i:44;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:2:"91";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:475:"<strong>Surviving the Holidays:</strong> A seasonal talk, based on Robin‚Äôs popular feature of the same title published in the Boston Globe Magazine in December 2006.  She addresses the so-called War on Christmas, ‚ÄúHappy Holidays,‚Äù how to cope with unrealistic expectations (others‚Äô and one‚Äôs own), and making the holidays fun rather than a chore.
 
