 to being an avid reader and The New York Times bestselling author.  Simone‚Äôs path is a unique and inspirational story that everyone can relate to ‚Äì from teens to adult.  This is a hilarious session where Simone will talk about how she got into writing, the funny and crazy things that happened to her along the way in her writing career, how she got published, how she comes up with ideas for books and book trailers, how her book covers are designed, and the very interesting research she‚Äôs done (which includes going to a juvenile detention center and going into ‚Äúgang territory‚Äù).  Participants will come out of this session motivated, inspired, and laughing.";}i:1256;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:295:"<strong>Insider's Look into a YA Bestseller:</strong> The New York Times and USA Today best-selling author Simone Elkeles shares her hilarious journey clawing her way from midlist to national bestsellerdom, sharing creative ideas for authors to increase their chances to become bestsellers, too.";}i:1257;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:368:"<strong>Let's Talk Teen Romance! She'll talk about ‚Äúwho‚Äôs buying what‚Äù, YA project taboos,</strong> how YA book covers can boost book sales, and voice/dialogue in young adult fiction. She'll also talk about essential elements she puts into her young adult novels. And, most importantly, she‚Äôll talk candidly about what you can do to break into this hot market.";}i:1258;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:328:"<strong>Writing Timeless Teen Dialogue:</strong> Simone Elkeles will show you how to write humorous, active, realistic dialogue in your teen manuscripts. She‚Äôll give examples of teen dialogue that works and what doesn‚Äôt work, along with exercises on using dialogue and internal thoughts to create realistic teen cha