oughtful. Most of all Ben loves people. He stays with the group for a long time after his speeches... and he‚Äôs there before for them, too.";}i:6707;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:34:"Visit Ben Stein's official website";}i:6708;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:17:"www.macmillan.com";}i:6709;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:24:"http://www.benstein.com/";}i:6710;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:25:"http://www.macmillan.com/";}i:6711;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:12:"videos_video";s:10:"meta_value";s:43:"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TLfc3IfjIO0";}i:6712;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"videos_description";s:10:"meta_value";s:55:"Ben Stein at Texas ACG Capital Connection in March 2011";}i:6713;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"biography_first_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6714;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:19:"biography_last_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6715;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"biography_upload_pdf";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6716;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:12:"photo_credit";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6717;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"511";s:8:"meta_key";s:14:"reviews_review";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6718;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"bwps_enable_ssl";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6719;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:16:"custom_permalink";s:10:"meta_value";s:9:"bethdoane";}i:6720;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"_wp_mf_page_template";s:10:"meta_value";s:7:"default";}i:6721;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:13:"works_product";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:6722;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:1184:"<strong>Living Your Dream:</strong> Born to an alcoholic and drug-addicted single mother in a small Ohio town, Beth was given up for adoption as a baby. Today she is an internationally recognized author, humanitarian, and social entrepreneur who founded her first company at age 22. Beth‚Äôs personal journey is proof that where we come from does not have to determine where we are going.

 
With no background in business, sales, or marketing, Beth launched the import and fashion-distribution company Andira International, and after witnessing the human rights violations and environmental pollution in apparel manufacturing, she grew her vision of a brand that gives back into an iconic line of apparel that launched at Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week. In this compelling and emotional speech, she explains how following her dreams is more about listening to our hearts than what others may say. She shares how her many mistakes, adventures, and misfortunes led to her greatest achievements.

 
Today, Beth helps major corporations make a difference through her consulting firm and shows us all how we can change the world when we put people before profit and follow our passion. ";}i:6723;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:931:"<strong>A Sustainable Future:</strong> Humanity is facing a global, environmental, and economic meltdown and Beth has experienced firsthand what this means for humanity. The immense environmental pollution and brutal human rights violations she witnessed while working in the fashion industry led her to create a socially conscious company that took her from fashion runways to saving rainforests. Those experiences changed not just her career but her entire life.
 
Beth‚Äôs story is a riveting look at how corporate corruption and greed are devouring our hope of a sustainable future and why we need to act now. Launching a consulting firm focused on sustainability, and supporting the largest environmental court case in history, made Beth an unlikely hero of the environmental movement, and in this thrilling speech, Beth shares a profound message of courage, action, and hope that will lead us to a truly sustainable future.";}i:6724;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"211";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:1034:"<strong>Going Tribal:</strong> Against all odds, Beth Doane created a brand designed to give back. This decision catapulted her on a journey that has led her to some of the most remote areas of the world. While working with indigenous cultures across Africa, the Amazon, and Central America, Beth discovered that we could revolutionize the way we run our businesses, non-profits, and even our lives in order to experience deep fulfillment, create exceptional products and services, and increase profits ‚Äì all while changing the world for the better.
 
