</tbody></table>";}i:7004;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:945:"<strong>A Master Class in Scent:</strong> Chandler's enthralling, riveting class hosted over a fabulous dinner at both corporate and private functions and in coordination with restaurants and hotels across the globe.  These highly interactive events are one of a kind: Chandler pairs the raw elements of les parfums gourmands, the great culinary perfumes, with fabulous culinary creations.  They are in fact two parallel dinners--the first created by Chandler, The New York Times perfume critic, as an invisible, olfactory meal to be consumed by the nose: essences and absolutes of black pepper, saffron, wine, cinnamon, mango--a host of elements that the great perfumers of the world use to create their scents.  The second is the physical meal, paired with each olfactory course, created by Chandler in coordination with the chef.  Macmillan Speakers is pleased to coordinate all details surrounding Chandler's Master Class with our clients.  ";}i:7005;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:298:"<strong>A History of Perfume:</strong> Chandler, the world's preeminent expert on perfume, presents a wonderful, interactive course on the history of perfume, offering pairings with great works of art and music, and offering perfume as an art form on par with the other great artistic traditions.  ";}i:7006;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:248:"<strong>The Perfect Scent:</strong> Chandler discusses his inside look at the perfume industry, based on his critically acclaimed book, The Perfect Scent.  Chandler has access and insight into the industry unmatched by perhaps any person on earth. ";}i:7007;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:38:"Visit Chandler Burr's official website";}i:7008;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:55:"Check out Chandler's New York Times blog, "Scent Notes"";}i:7009;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:60:"Listen to Chandler's interview with NPR on The Perfect Scent";}i:7010;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:17:"www.macmillan.com";}i:7011;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:17:"More Speaker Info";}i:7012;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:45:"http://www.chandlerburr.com/newsite/index.htm";}i:7013;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:56:"http://themoment.blogs.nytimes.com/author/chandler-burr/";}i:7014;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:61:"http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=18238465";}i:7015;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:25:"http://www.macmillan.com/";}i:7016;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:49:"http://us.macmillan.com/author/chandlerburr#works";}i:7017;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:12:"videos_video";s:10:"meta_value";s:67:"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K3Df_g7ZAvc&feature=player_embedded";}i:7018;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"videos_description";s:10:"meta_value";s:37:"New York Times Video on Chandler Burr";}i:7019;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"biography_first_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:7020;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"170";s:8:"meta_key";s:19:"biograp