 information about your health? Dr. Wen provides dos and don‚Äôts for safely, effectively, and quickly using the Internet to improve your care.";}i:7433;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:264:"<strong>10 Truths and Myths of Modern Healthcare</strong> Today‚Äôs news is filled with conflicting information about what to do with your health. Dr. Wen breaks it down and tells you about the 10 Truths and Myths, and what you can do today to improve your health.";}i:7434;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:325:"<strong>Living with Chronic Disease: What You Need to Know to Get the Best Care</strong> from Your Doctor In this talk, Dr. Wen addresses the patient with chronic disease as well as the family member and caregiver. She provides everyday tips and discusses specific ways to improve interactions with your healthcare providers.";}i:7435;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:255:"<strong>The Woman‚Äôs Guide to Healthy Living and Better Health</strong> Tailored to different groups of women, this talk provides practical suggestions that listeners can incorporate into their daily life to work towards healthy living and better health.";}i:7436;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:193:"<strong>"My Body is . . ." Dr.</strong> Wen tailors this talk specifically to youth and women‚Äôs groups. Topics discussed include fostering a positive body image and connecting with your body.";}i:7437;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:152:"<strong>Seize the World and Make It Yours!</strong> A talk to youth leaders about seizing opportunities and making a difference in the world around you.";}i:7438;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"577";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:1