r how many people you've led, this will forever enhance the way you think about leadership.  Not only the way you lead at work, at home, or in your community, but even the way you lead yourself. 

Each person who attends this event can expect to:

- Be inspired with a new perspective about the impact you can have in the workplace and across the world.
- Learn a proven method to increase profitability and improve performance, by enhancing your life and the lives of the people who work for/with you.
- Walk away with a step by step approach for creating a culture where people never want to leave.
- Discover the two factors that determine whether a leader achieves remarkable success, or perpetual mediocrity.
- Understand why you can't be an effective CEO if you don't understand C+E<O.
- Have at least one major leadership and life epiphany.

The Big Five for Life: The Secret of Personal Growth: What if every moment of your day was focused on helping you with the five most important things you want to do, see, or experience during your lifetime?  What would your days be like?  What would your life be like?  Why does it matter if you know them?

Those five things are your Big Five for Life‚Ñ¢.  Your awareness of them, and progress towards them, will determine whether or not your life is a success or a failure, in your own eyes.

Each person who attends this session can expect to:
- Learn to take the life you wish for, and make it the life you live.
- Gain clarity about your place in life and the world.
- Find ways to get paid for doing what you love. 
- Have your perspective about life significantly altered in a positive way.";}i:8227;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:38:"Find out more on The Big Five for Life";}i:8228;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:17:"www.macmillan.com";}i:8229;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:30:"http://www.bigfiveforlife.com/";}i:8230;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"related_links_link";s:10:"meta_value";s:25:"http://www.macmillan.com/";}i:8231;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:12:"videos_video";s:10:"meta_value";s:66:"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7u5FoUxy9a8&feature=player_embedded";}i:8232;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:18:"videos_description";s:10:"meta_value";s:24:"John Strelecky Interview";}i:8233;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"biography_first_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:8234;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:19:"biography_last_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:8235;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"biography_upload_pdf";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:8236;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:12:"photo_credit";s:10:"meta_value";s:21:"Photo: Cindy Xin Zhao";}i:8237;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"518";s:8:"meta_key";s:14:"reviews_review";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:8238;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"119";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"bwps_enable_ssl";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:8239;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"119";s:8:"meta_key";s:16:"custom_permalink";s:10:"meta_value";s:10:"johnubacon";}i:8240;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"119";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"_wp_mf_page_template";s:10:"meta_value";s:7:"default";}i:8241;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"119";s:8:"me