</tbody></table>";}i:8979;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:363:"<strong>Autism in Education:</strong> As a teacher with more than a decade of experience working with autistic children, Matthew has developed insights and strategies for assisting autistic and special needs students realize success in the classroom. Through storytelling and humor, he shares these insights with teachers, parents and special needs advocates.    ";}i:8980;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:401:"<strong>Arts in Education:</strong> For the past 15 years, Matthew has integrated theater, music, the visual arts and more into the classroom using authentic and highly effective teaching strategies. He speaks to audiences of educators and parents about how to integrate the arts seamlessly into a classroom in order to provide a richer, more meaningful and more instructive experience for children.  ";}i:8981;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:335:"<strong>Shakespeare for the Elementary School Student:</strong> Matthew has been teaching Shakespeare to elementary school students for the past fifteen years, using the original text. Through storytelling and humor, Matthew discusses the process by which Shakespeare became an integral part of his classroom and his students‚Äô lives.";}i:8982;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:334:"<strong>Parenting Made Easy (or at Least, Easier):</strong> It‚Äôs a bold statement to make, but Matthew believes that for most parents, it can be a reality. Utilizing his experience as a parent, a former step-parent and a teacher, he speaks about simple but effective strategies to make parenting easier and (more importantly) fun.  ";}i:8983;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:254:"<strong>Family Life:</strong> A successful family life depends upon the relationships within the home. Matthew‚Äôs talk deals with strategies for strengthening these relationships and streamlining the household operation for the benefit of all involved. ";}i:8984;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:228:"<strong>Everyone Can and Should Be Writing:</strong> Though it makes his editor crazy when he says this, Matthew believes that everyone can and should be writing. This talk seeks to inspire and inform audiences to do just that. ";}i:8985;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:269:"<strong>How to Launch Your Career as an Author:</strong> Looking to begin a writing career? Matthew offers practical advice and insight into the world of publishing, as well as the means by which amateur writers can earn their first book contract or paid writing gig.  ";}i:8986;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"speeches_speech";s:10:"meta_value";s:132:"<strong>The Writing Process:</strong> Discover the myriad of ways that writers work, including those not spoken about nearly enough.";}i:8987;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:53:"Visit Matthew Dicks‚Äô official website to learn more";}i:8988;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:64:"Watch Matthew Dicks‚Äô Moth Performance on Theft (Kids‚Äô Shoes)";}i:8989;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:89:"Watch Matthew Dicks‚Äô Moth Performance on Ego (Life Lessons Learned While Pole Vaulting)";}i:8990;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"941";s:8:"meta_key";s:23:"related_links_link_name";s:10:"meta_value";s:55:"Read a profile of Matthew Dicks in the Hartford Couran